            "title": "Old Testament Reading",
            "api_nlt_to_ref": "Judges.7:1-8:17",
            "value": "%3Cdiv%20class%3D%22%20NLT%20NLT%20BibleText%20section%22%3E%3Csection%3E%3Ch2%20class%3D%22bk_ch_vs_header%22%3EJudges%207%3A1-8%3A17%2C%20NLT%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22judg_7_1%22%20bk%3D%22judg%22%20ch%3D%227%22%20vn%3D%221%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22chapter-number%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw%22%3EJudges%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw_ch%22%3E7%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EGideon%20Defeats%20the%20Midianites%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-ch-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E1%3C%2Fspan%3ESo%20Jerub-baal%20(that%20is%2C%20Gideon)%20and%20his%20army%20got%20up%20early%20and%20went%20as%20far%20as%20the%20spring%20of%20Harod.%20The%20armies%20of%20Midian%20were%20camped%20north%20of%20them%20in%20the%20valley%20near%20the%20hill%20of%20Moreh.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22judg_7_2%22%20bk%3D%22judg%22%20ch%3D%227%22%20vn%3D%222%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20said%20to%20Gideon%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BYou%20have%20too%20many%20warriors%20with%20you.%20If%20I%20let%20all%20of%20you%20fight%20the%20Midianites%2C%20the%20Israelites%20will%20boast%20to%20me%20that%20they%20saved%20themselves%20by%20their%20own%20strength.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22judg_7_3%22%20bk%3D%22judg%22%20ch%3D%227%22%20vn%3D%223%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E3%3C%2Fspan%3ETherefore%2C%20tell%20the%20people%2C%20%26%23x2018%3BWhoever%20is%20timid%20or%20afraid%20may%20leave%20this%20mountain%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E7%3A3%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3Emay%20leave%20Mount%20Gilead.%3C%2Fem%3E%20The%20identity%20of%20Mount%20Gilead%20is%20uncertain%20in%20this%20context.%20It%20is%20perhaps%20used%20here%20as%20another%20name%20for%20Mount%20Gilboa.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20and%20go%20home.%26%23x2019%3B%26%23x201D%3B%20So%2022%2C000%20of%20them%20went%20home%2C%20leaving%20only%2010%2C000%20who%20were%20willing%20to%20fight.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22judg_7_4%22%20bk%3D%22judg%22%20ch%3D%227%22%20vn%3D%224%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E4%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20told%20Gideon%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BThere%20are%20still%20too%20many!%20Bring%20them%20down%20to%20the%20spring%2C%20and%20I%20will%20test%20them%20to%20determine%20who%20will%20go%20with%20you%20and%20who%20will%20not.%26%23x201D%3B%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22judg_7_5%22%20bk%3D%22judg%22%20ch%3D%227%22%20vn%3D%225%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E5%3C%2Fspan%3EWhen%20Gideon%20took%20his%20warriors%20down%20to%20the%20water%2C%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20told%20him%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BDivide%20the%20men%20into%20two%20groups.%20In%20one%20group%20put%20all%20those%20who%20cup%20water%20in%20their%20hands%20and%20lap%20it%20up%20with%20their%20tongues%20like%20dogs.%20In%20the%20other%20group%20put%20all%20those%20who%20kneel%20down%20and%20drink%20with%20their%20mouths%20in%20the%20stream.%26%23x201D%3B%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22judg_7_6%22%20bk%3D%22judg%22%20ch%3D%227%22%20vn%3D%226%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E6%3C%2Fspan%3EOnly%20300%26%23xA0%3Bof%20the%20men%20drank%20from%20their%20hands.%20All%20the%20others%20got%20down%20on%20their%20knees%20and%20drank%20with%20their%20mouths%20in%20the%20stream.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22judg_7_7%22%20bk%3D%22judg%22%20ch%3D%227%22%20vn%3D%227%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E7%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20told%20Gideon%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BWith%20these%20300%26%23xA0%3Bmen%20I%20will%20rescue%20you%20and%20give%20you%20victory%20over%20the%20Midianites.%20Send%20all%20the%20others%20home.%26%23x201D%3B%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22judg_7_8%22%20bk%3D%22judg%22%20ch%3D%227%22%20vn%3D%228%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E8%3C%2Fspan%3ESo%20Gideon%20collected%20the%20provisions%20and%20rams%26%23x2019%3B%20horns%20of%20the%20other%20warriors%20and%20sent%20them%20home.%20But%20he%20kept%20the%20300%26%23xA0%3Bmen%20with%20him.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3EThe%20Midianite%20camp%20was%20in%20the%20valley%20just%20below%20Gideon.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22judg_7_9%22%20bk%3D%22judg%22%20ch%3D%227%22%20vn%3D%229%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E9%3C%2Fspan%3EThat%20night%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20said%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BGet%20up!%20Go%20down%20into%20the%20Midianite%20camp%2C%20for%20I%20have%20given%20you%20victory%20over%20them!%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22judg_7_10%22%20bk%3D%22judg%22%20ch%3D%227%22%20vn%3D%2210%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E10%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20if%20you%20are%20afraid%20to%20attack%2C%20go%20down%20to%20the%20camp%20with%20your%20servant%20Purah.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22judg_7_11%22%20bk%3D%22judg%22%20ch%3D%227%22%20vn%3D%2211%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E11%3C%2Fspan%3EListen%20to%20what%20the%20Midianites%20are%20saying%2C%20and%20you%20will%20be%20greatly%20encouraged.%20Then%20you%20will%20be%20eager%20to%20attack.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3ESo%20Gideon%20took%20Purah%20and%20went%20down%20to%20the%20edge%20of%20the%20enemy%20camp.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22judg_7_12%22%20bk%3D%22judg%22%20ch%3D%227%22%20vn%3D%2212%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E12%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20armies%20of%20Midian%2C%20Amalek%2C%20and%20the%20people%20of%20the%20east%20had%20settled%20in%20the%20valley%20like%20a%20swarm%20of%20locusts.%20Their%20camels%20were%20like%20grains%20of%20sand%20on%20the%20seashore%26%23x2014%3Btoo%20many%20to%20count!%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22judg_7_13%22%20bk%3D%22judg%22%20ch%3D%227%22%20vn%3D%2213%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E13%3C%2Fspan%3EGideon%20crept%20up%20just%20as%20a%20man%20was%20telling%20his%20companion%20about%20a%20dream.%20The%20man%20said%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BI%20had%20this%20dream%2C%20and%20in%20my%20dream%20a%20loaf%20of%20barley%20bread%20came%20tumbling%20down%20into%20the%20Midianite%20camp.%20It%20hit%20a%20tent%2C%20turned%20it%20over%2C%20and%20knocked%20it%20flat!%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22judg_7_14%22%20bk%3D%22judg%22%20ch%3D%227%22%20vn%3D%2214%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E14%3C%2Fspan%3EHis%20companion%20answered%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BYour%20dream%20can%20mean%20only%20one%20thing%26%23x2014%3BGod%20has%20given%20Gideon%20son%20of%20Joash%2C%20the%20Israelite%2C%20victory%20over%20Midian%20and%20all%20its%20allies!%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22judg_7_15%22%20bk%3D%22judg%22%20ch%3D%227%22%20vn%3D%2215%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E15%3C%2Fspan%3EWhen%20Gideon%20heard%20the%20dream%20and%20its%20interpretation%2C%20he%20bowed%20in%20worship%20before%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E.%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E7%3A15%3C%2Fspan%3E%20As%20in%20Greek%20version%3B%20Hebrew%20reads%20%3Cem%3Ehe%20bowed.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Then%20he%20returned%20to%20the%20Israelite%20camp%20and%20shouted%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BGet%20up!%20For%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20has%20given%20you%20victory%20over%20the%20Midianite%20hordes!%26%23x201D%3B%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22judg_7_16%22%20bk%3D%22judg%22%20ch%3D%227%22%20vn%3D%2216%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E16%3C%2Fspan%3EHe%20divided%20the%20300%26%23xA0%3Bmen%20into%20three%20groups%20and%20gave%20each%20man%20a%20ram%26%23x2019%3Bs%20horn%20and%20a%20clay%20jar%20with%20a%20torch%20in%20it.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22judg_7_17%22%20bk%3D%22judg%22%20ch%3D%227%22%20vn%3D%2217%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E17%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20he%20said%20to%20them%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BKeep%20your%20eyes%20on%20me.%20When%20I%20come%20to%20the%20edge%20of%20the%20camp%2C%20do%20just%20as%20I%20do.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22judg_7_18%22%20bk%3D%22judg%22%20ch%3D%227%22%20vn%3D%2218%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E18%3C%2Fspan%3EAs%20soon%20as%20I%20and%20those%20with%20me%20blow%20the%20rams%26%23x2019%3B%20horns%2C%20blow%20your%20horns%2C%20too%2C%20all%20around%20the%20entire%20camp%2C%20and%20shout%2C%20%26%23x2018%3BFor%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20and%20for%20Gideon!%26%23x2019%3B%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22judg_7_19%22%20bk%3D%22judg%22%20ch%3D%227%22%20vn%3D%2219%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E19%3C%2Fspan%3EIt%20was%20just%20after%20midnight%2C%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E7%3A19%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3Eat%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%20second%20watch.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20after%20the%20changing%20of%20the%20guard%2C%20when%20Gideon%20and%20the%20100%26%23xA0%3Bmen%20with%20him%20reached%20the%20edge%20of%20the%20Midianite%20camp.%20Suddenly%2C%20they%20blew%20the%20rams%26%23x2019%3B%20horns%20and%20broke%20their%20clay%20jars.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22judg_7_20%22%20bk%3D%22judg%22%20ch%3D%227%22%20vn%3D%2220%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E20%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20all%20three%20groups%20blew%20their%20horns%20and%20broke%20their%20jars.%20They%20held%20the%20blazing%20torches%20in%20their%20left%20hands%20and%20the%20horns%20in%20their%20right%20hands%2C%20and%20they%20all%20shouted%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BA%20sword%20for%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20and%20for%20Gideon!%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22judg_7_21%22%20bk%3D%22judg%22%20ch%3D%227%22%20vn%3D%2221%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E21%3C%2Fspan%3EEach%20man%20stood%20at%20his%20position%20around%20the%20camp%20and%20watched%20as%20all%20the%20Midianites%20rushed%20around%20in%20a%20panic%2C%20shouting%20as%20they%20ran%20to%20escape.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22judg_7_22%22%20bk%3D%22judg%22%20ch%3D%227%22%20vn%3D%2222%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E22%3C%2Fspan%3EWhen%20the%20300%26%23xA0%3BIsraelites%20blew%20their%20rams%26%23x2019%3B%20horns%2C%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20caused%20the%20warriors%20in%20the%20camp%20to%20fight%20against%20each%20other%20with%20their%20swords.%20Those%20who%20were%20not%20killed%20fled%20to%20places%20as%20far%20away%20as%20Beth-shittah%20near%20Zererah%20and%20to%20the%20border%20of%20Abel-meholah%20near%20Tabbath.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22judg_7_23%22%20bk%3D%22judg%22%20ch%3D%227%22%20vn%3D%2223%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E23%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20Gideon%20sent%20for%20the%20warriors%20of%20Naphtali%2C%20Asher%2C%20and%20Manasseh%2C%20who%20joined%20in%20chasing%20the%20army%20of%20Midian.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22judg_7_24%22%20bk%3D%22judg%22%20ch%3D%227%22%20vn%3D%2224%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E24%3C%2Fspan%3EGideon%20also%20sent%20messengers%20throughout%20the%20hill%20country%20of%20Ephraim%2C%20saying%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BCome%20down%20to%20attack%20the%20Midianites.%20Cut%20them%20off%20at%20the%20shallow%20crossings%20of%20the